sql:
SELECT aqs_parameter_desc 
FROM aqs_parameters 
WHERE aqs_parameter_code = 42401;

SELECT site_id
FROM sites
WHERE state_id = (SELECT MIN(state_id) FROM states);

SELECT site_name
FROM sites
ORDER BY site_name ASC;

SELECT DISTINCT s.site_name 
FROM sites s
INNER JOIN air_quality_data aqd ON s.site_id = aqd.site_id;

external_knowledge:
SO2 refers to sulfur dioxide; AQI stands for Air Quality Index, which measures air pollution levels and health impacts; 'monitoring sites' are specific locations where environmental data is collected.;
The concentrations are summed daily for each site to account for variations throughout the day. The 'units' refer to the measurement scale used for SO2 concentration, commonly parts per billion (ppb).;
The year 2022 is the time frame for data collection, meaning only entries from that year are considered. The 'locations' are determined by the site's latitude and longitude, which identify precise geographical coordinates.;
